From 5cbf290b79351971f20c7a533247e8d58a3f970c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 14:45:42 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: ISO: Fix not releasing hdev reference on iso_conn_big_sync
Git-commit: 5cbf290b79351971f20c7a533247e8d58a3f970c
Patch-mainline: v7.1-rc7
References: git-fixes

hci_get_route() returns a reference-counted hci_dev pointer via
hci_dev_hold(). The function exits normally or with an error without ever
releasing it.

Fixes: 07a9342b94a9 ("Bluetooth: ISO: Send BIG Create Sync via hci_sync")
Reported-by: Sashiko <sashiko-bot@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 net/bluetooth/iso.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/bluetooth/iso.c b/net/bluetooth/iso.c
index 876649556d3c..3d707c43bdc0 100644
--- a/net/bluetooth/iso.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/iso.c
@@ -1595,6 +1595,7 @@ static void iso_conn_big_sync(struct sock *sk)
 
 	release_sock(sk);
 	hci_dev_unlock(hdev);
+	hci_dev_put(hdev);
 }
 
 static int iso_sock_recvmsg(struct socket *sock, struct msghdr *msg,
-- 
2.54.0

